dct_title_s: 1653-1664, Amsterdam in New Netherland : the city of the Dutch West India Company
dct_description_sm: Relief shown by hachures. Shows the footprints of some historic buildings and names them; roads and wharves are also named. "The personal names are those of the more prominent citizens of that period with the location of their homes." "The principal points of interest for this period are in red." Includes historical notes. This is one map from the set titled: Early New York.
